Package edu.cnm.deepdive.rps.service

Class EcosystemRepository

java.lang.Object
edu.cnm.deepdive.rps.service.EcosystemRepository
@Singleton public class EcosystemRepository extends Object
Manages and choreographs creation of, and subsequent operations performed on (and results returned from) a simulation involving an instance of Ecosystem. Any mutation operations performed on an ecosystem should be coordinated through an instance of this class, not by direct invocation of mutator methods on the Ecosystem instance itself.

  • Method Details

    • create

      public Single<Ecosystem> create(int numBreeds, int size, boolean toroidal)
      Creates and returns a Single<Ecosystem> which—when subscribed to—creates an instance of Ecosystem and updates the value in the LiveData<Ecosystem> container returned by getEcosystem().
      • The ecosystem terrain will be populated with approximately equal numbers of each breed, with the total number of breeds specified by numBreeds.
      • The ecosystem's terrain is a lattice or grid, with height and width specified by size, and with each cell occupied by an individual of one of the breeds.
      • The terrain may be thought of as a square box with closed sides, or as a torus with wrapping edges, depending on the value of the toroidal parameter.
      Parameters:
      numBreeds - Initial number of breeds inhabiting the terrain of the ecosystem.
      size - Height and width of the terrain.
      toroidal - Flag specifying whether the terrain is a torus (true) or box (false.
      Returns:
      Single<Ecosystem> that can be subscribed to, to create an Ecosystem.

    • run

      public Observable<Integer> run(int iterationsPerBatch, float swapProbability, int millisecondsBetweenBatches) throws IllegalStateException
      Creates and returns an Observable<Integer> which—when subscribed to—starts execution of the ecosystem simulation.
      • Each onNext event of the Observable consists of an invocation of Ecosystem.iterate(iterationsPerBatch, swapProbability).
      • The value passed to the subscribing Consumer<Integer> is the number of iterations in the batch in which a competitive interaction resulted in replacement of the losing individual by a copy of the winning individual.
      • At the end of each batch of iterations, if the ecosystem has reached the absorbing state (in which only a single breed is surviving), the onComplete event is triggered automatically.
      Parameters:
      iterationsPerBatch - Iterations of the simulation executed for each onNext.
      swapProbability - Probability that a randomly selected pair is swapped at the start of each iteration.
      millisecondsBetweenBatches - Milliseconds by which each batch of iterations follows completion of the previous batch.
      Returns:
      Observable<Integer> that can be subscribed to, to start execution of the simulation.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - If the Ecosystem has not yet been created, or if it is already in the absorbing state.

    • pause

      public Completable pause()
      Creates and returns a Completable which—when subscribed to—pauses execution of the simulation. As a result of pausing the simulation, the onComplete event is triggered for the Observable<Integer> returned by the run(int, float, int) method.
      Returns:
      Completable that can be subscribed to, to pause execution of the simulation.
